Speaker 1: Hi, this is Iagra.

Speaker 2: Yeah, is this a live person?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: Oh, well, good. About time.

Speaker 1: Hi, how can I help you, sir?

Speaker 1: Oh, okay. So it says generic on the bottle, and the PIN says what, AC340?

Speaker 2: No, it just says generic.

Speaker 1: On the bottle, you should have a code. I'm just curious. It says AC340 on the bottle or on the single PIN?

Speaker 2: The number on that is 600-107-08.

Speaker 1: On the actual field, what do you see, the small field, if you don't mind checking?

Speaker 2: I'm checking here. Verified by ZOB. Dispense. Discard.

Speaker 1: No, on the actual field, if you can grab the small field in the bottle, there is something engraved on the field.

Speaker 2: On the field itself?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: I thought it was supposed to say AGV on that, but it also said, in your advertising, it says to be ready in 11 minutes, and this says over an hour.

Speaker 1: I think it's something like a bait and switch here.

Speaker 2: What did it just say, sir?

Speaker 1: Let me see if I can read this. I've got to get a magnifying glass.

Speaker 2: Yeah, no, that's regular generic. I can send you a replacement with AGV. The PIN is going to say 5-0. That's the improved formula.

Speaker 1: On the bottle, usually as a standard, you always say it's a benefit of one hour, because that's just standard. That doesn't matter, but the code on the PIN will matter.

Speaker 2: So the one I send you is going to say 5-0, that's the AGV.

Speaker 1: Why on the advertising, in the RU literature, it says 11 minutes? It sounds like a bait and switch.

Speaker 2: Yeah, because that's why it works. It works in 11 minutes, but the standard of the industry is to put one hour just on the bottle, just as a standard, because everybody is different.

Speaker 1: So they put a large window, but that new formula has been proven to have the fastest activation than anything before.

Speaker 2: And then what you have is actually regular generic, so I need to replace that by the actual AGV, if you like.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I think the new stuff, and then bingo, I get this generic stuff.

Speaker 2: All right, let's move forward, sir. I understood your concern, but we have a solution here, okay?

Speaker 1: I don't know why your order came and corrected at the pharmacy here for some reason, from what I see here, but I can correct that for you.

Speaker 2: We can move forward. We have some AGV in stock that I can send to you, if you like.

Speaker 1: Okay, I appreciate it. Yes.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: All right, so now the pill is going to say 5-0. It's a different formula.

Speaker 1: Keep those that you have right now as a backup, and FBI approved, made between the U.S. and France.

Speaker 2: You don't need to return it. Get it as a backup, and I'm just going to send you the replacement on top of that.

Speaker 1: So that's going to be a total of 20 pills, okay?

Speaker 2: Okay, all right.

Speaker 1: All right, yeah.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: So I sent the replacement, okay, a low 2 to 5 business day, you will get it.

Speaker 2: The pill is going to have a different medical code on it, because the one that you will receive after is an improved formula, okay?

Speaker 1: Okay, all right.

Speaker 2: And try it, and I hope that can be a good help for you, okay?

Speaker 1: All right. Do you have my name and address, sir?

Speaker 2: Yes, Mr. Charles Arlen in 175-145 Street, Seton, Illinois.

Speaker 1: Correct, yes, all right.

Speaker 2: All right, yeah.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: You're all set.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Of course.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Bye.
